@NODE "Design" "AmigaDOS For Beginners - Using AmigaDOS For Beginners - Article Design"

@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}AMIGADOS FOR BEGINNERS

USING AMIGADOS FOR BEGINNERS - ARTICLE DESIGN@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
The contents of "AmigaDOS For Beginners" are split into various articles.
Some articles will deal with only one topic or command. Other parts will
deal with a number of related commands. In all cases I have tried to make
the individual parts as logical and as self contained as possible.

The articles are held in directories named for the numbers of the articles
they hold. For example:-

  Directory name:- Parts_01-10
  Holds articles:- 1 to 10

All @{"examples scripts" LINK "Examples"} relating to an article are held in the same directory
as the article.


